# Building Models

Tensors, layers, datasets, loaders, losses, optimizers, and short training runs. Details that become
proof-relevant later—shapes in types, parameter payloads, batch layout, loss choice—are introduced
here as ordinary ML engineering, not re-taught as verification philosophy.

