# Runtime, Autograd, and Interop

Eager execution, compiled graphs, autograd, optimizers, checkpoints, and PyTorch interop. Backends
choose how to compute; they are not new mathematical models. Claim vocabulary from the Introduction
still applies: a run, a check, and a theorem remain different kinds of support.

